        "title": "Javafx and combobox",
        "body": "<p>I have an int variable (modID) from a selected tablecolumn. I would like to use this variable to search a two column combobox (int modelID, String model), match the modelID column of the combobox and display the corresponding model value.<\/p>\n\n<p>Class used to construct the combobox.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>package batteryOrdering.order;\n\npublic class ModelList {\n    private int modelID;\n    private int manufacturerID;\n    private String model;\n\n    public ModelList(int modelID, String model) {\n        this.modelID = modelID;\n        this.manufacturerID = manufacturerID;\n        this.model = model;\n    }\n\n    public int getModelID() {\n        return modelID;\n    }\n\n    public int getManufacturerID() {\n        return manufacturerID;\n    }\n\n    public String getModel() {\n        return model;\n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>The following code matches against the combobox index and not the ID column. What is wrong?<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>modelCombobox.getSelectionModel().select(modID);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
